## 3a. Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase. Hooks: `use` + camelCase. Utils: camelCase. Constants: UPPER_SNAKE or object. Types: PascalCase.

## 3b. Utils, Constants, Endpoints

**Utils** (`shared/utils/`): Pure helpers вЂ” `format.ts`, `cn.ts`, `storage.ts`.

**Constants** (`shared/constants/`): `routes.ts`, `keys.ts`, `limits.ts`.

**ROUTES** (path strings for navigation):

```ts
export const ROUTES = { HOME: '/', LOGIN: '/login', DASHBOARD: '/dashboard' } as const
```

**Endpoints** (`shared/constants/endpoints.ts`):

```ts
export const ENDPOINTS = {
  AUTH: { LOGIN: '/auth/login', ME: '/auth/me' },
  USERS: { LIST: '/users', BY_ID: (id: string) => `/users/${id}` }
} as const
```

## 3c. Path Aliases

`tsconfig.json`: `"paths": { "@/*": ["./src/*"] }`. Optional: `@features`, `@shared`, `@services`.

## 3d. Barrel Exports

Use `index.ts` in shared folders. Prefer direct imports for large modules.

## 3e. Responsive Design & Theming

Mobile-first. Tailwind breakpoints. Theming: Context/Redux; CSS vars; `data-theme="dark"`; `prefers-color-scheme` for initial load.

## 3f. next.config.js

Configure images, rewrites, env:

```js
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
export default {
  images: { remotePatterns: [{ protocol: 'https', hostname: 'cdn.example.com' }] },
  env: { NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL }
}
```

## 3g. i18n (Optional)

Use `next-intl` or `react-i18next` with `next.config` rewrites for locale prefixes. Store translations in `messages/{lang}.json`.

## 4. Environment Variables

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.example.com
```

```ts
export const env = { apiUrl: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL ?? "" }
```

Never use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` for secrets. Use `.env`, `.env.development`, `.env.production`.

## 5. TypeScript Rules

`strict`, `noImplicitAny`, `strictNullChecks`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`. Avoid `any`; use Zod for API contracts.

## 7. Routing (App Router)

```
app/
в”њв”Ђ page.tsx
в”њв”Ђ dashboard/
в”‚  в””в”Ђ page.tsx
в””в”Ђ blog/
   в””в”Ђ [slug]/
      в””в”Ђ page.tsx
```

## 7a. Server vs Client Components

- **Server** (default): No `'use client'`; render on server; async; fetch in component; no `useState`, `useEffect`, event handlers, or browser APIs.
- **Client**: Add `'use client'` at top of file; render in browser; use hooks, React Query, `onClick`, etc. Import only from Serverв†’Client; never import Client into Server (use composition).

## 7b. Layouts

Root `app/layout.tsx`; nested `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` for shared chrome.

## 7c. Loading, Error, Not Found

- `loading.tsx`: Suspense boundary.
- `error.tsx`: Error boundary (Client); use `reset`.
- `not-found.tsx`: 404; call `notFound()` from Server Components.

## 7d. Middleware (Protected Routes)

```ts
// middleware.ts
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'

export function middleware(request: Request) {
  const token = request.cookies.get('auth-token')
  if (!token && request.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/dashboard')) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/login', request.url))
  }
  return NextResponse.next()
}

export const config = { matcher: ['/dashboard/:path*'] }
```

## 7e. Route Groups

`(auth)`, `(dashboard)` for layout grouping without affecting URL.

## 7f. generateMetadata

```ts
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const post = await fetchPost(params.slug)
  return { title: post.title, description: post.excerpt }
}
```

## 7g. Server Actions (Optional)

`'use server'` for mutations without API route. Prefer API routes for complex logic.

## 7h. generateStaticParams (SSG)

For static generation of dynamic routes:

```ts
export async function generateStaticParams() {
  const posts = await fetchPosts()
  return posts.map(p => ({ slug: p.slug }))
}
```

## 7i. next/link

Use `<Link href={...}>` for internal navigation instead of `<a>`. Enables prefetching and client-side transitions.

## 9. Providers Setup

`app/providers.tsx` (Client Component):

```tsx
'use client'
import { useState } from 'react'
import { Provider } from 'react-redux'
import { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from '@tanstack/react-query'
import { store } from '@/app/store'

export function Providers({ children }) {
  const [queryClient] = useState(() => new QueryClient())
  return (
    <Provider store={store}>
      <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>{children}</QueryClientProvider>
    </Provider>
  )
}
```

Use in root layout: `<Providers>{children}</Providers>`. Add `.nvmrc` or `engines` in `package.json` for Node version pinning.
